President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. The nominees include Jannette L. Dates for the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting and Geoffrey R. Pyatt for Ambassador to Ukraine. The appointees include Teresa Isabel Leger for the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation and Stephen L. Mayo for the National Science Board of the National Science Foundation. President Obama believes that these individuals will be valuable additions to his administration as they work together to address the challenges facing America.